external_ip.description: The external IPv4 assigned to the global fowarding rule.

external_ipv6_address.description: The external IPv6 assigned to the global fowarding rule.

http_proxy.description: The HTTP proxy used by this module.

https_proxy.description: The HTTPS proxy used by this module.

ipv6_enabled.description: Whether IPv6 configuration is enabled on this load-balancer

ssl_certificate_created.description: The SSL certificate create from key/pem

url_map.description: The default URL map used by this module.

address.description: Existing IPv4 address to use (the actual IP address value)

backends.description: Map backend indices to list of backend maps.

certificate.description: Content of the SSL certificate. Requires `ssl` to be set to `true` and `create_ssl_certificate` set to `true`

certificate_map.description: Certificate Map ID in format projects/{project}/locations/global/certificateMaps/{name}. Identifies a certificate map associated with the given target proxy.  Requires `ssl` to be set to `true`

create_address.description: Create a new global IPv4 address

create_ipv6_address.description: Allocate a new IPv6 address. Conflicts with "ipv6_address" - if both specified, "create_ipv6_address" takes precedence.

create_url_map.description: Set to `false` if url_map variable is provided.

edge_security_policy.description: The resource URL for the edge security policy to associate with the backend service

enable_ipv6.description: Enable IPv6 address on the CDN load-balancer

http_forward.description: Set to `false` to disable HTTP port 80 forward

https_redirect.description: Set to `true` to enable https redirect on the lb.

ipv6_address.description: An existing IPv6 address to use (the actual IP address value)

labels.description: The labels to attach to resources created by this module

load_balancing_scheme.description: Load balancing scheme type (EXTERNAL for classic external load balancer, EXTERNAL_MANAGED for Envoy-based load balancer, and INTERNAL_SELF_MANAGED for traffic director)

managed_ssl_certificate_domains.description: Create Google-managed SSL certificates for specified domains. Requires `ssl` to be set to `true`

name.description: Name for the forwarding rule and prefix for supporting resources

network.description: Network for INTERNAL_SELF_MANAGED load balancing scheme

private_key.description: Content of the private SSL key. Requires `ssl` to be set to `true` and `create_ssl_certificate` set to `true`

project.description: The project to deploy to, if not set the default provider project is used.

quic.description: Specifies the QUIC override policy for this resource. Set true to enable HTTP/3 and Google QUIC support, false to disable both. Defaults to null which enables support for HTTP/3 only.

random_certificate_suffix.description: Bool to enable/disable random certificate name generation. Set and keep this to true if you need to change the SSL cert.

security_policy.description: The resource URL for the security policy to associate with the backend service

server_tls_policy.description: The resource URL for the server TLS policy to associate with the https proxy service

ssl.description: Set to `true` to enable SSL support. If `true` then at least one of these are required: 1) `ssl_certificates` OR 2) `create_ssl_certificate` set to `true` and `private_key/certificate` OR  3) `managed_ssl_certificate_domains`, OR 4) `certificate_map`

ssl_certificates.description: SSL cert self_link list. Requires `ssl` to be set to `true`

url_map.description: The url_map resource to use. Default is to send all traffic to first backend.

domain.description: Domain name to run the load balancer on. Used if `ssl` is `true`.

lb_name.description: Name for load balancer and associated resources

region.description: Location for load balancer and Cloud Run resources

ssl.description: Run load balancer on HTTPS and provision managed certificate with provided `domain`.
